vegetables are softened and lightly blackened."},{"content":"Transfer roasted vegetables immediately into a ceramic or glass bowl and cover tightly with cling film. Leave to stand for 10 minutes."},{"content":"Remove roasted vegetables from bowl and transfer onto a plate covered with paper towel to drain. Gently peel skin from vegetables and discard skins. Transfer peeled vegetables back into bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place blanched almonds in mixing bowl and roast <b>8 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove lid and leave to cool in mixing bowl (approx. 5 minutes)."},{"content":"Add all remaining Romesco sauce ingredients, and reserved peeled vegetables, then blend <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then blend again <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer sauce into a bowl until ready to serve."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Meatballs"},{"content":"Place beef in mixing bowl and mince <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place chorizo, red onion, garlic, parsley and bread in mixing bowl then chop <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/6-7 times<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add nutmeg, paprika, salt, pepper, egg and reserved mince then blend <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>. Roll mixture into walnut-sized meatballs, to make approx. 30, and set aside."},{"content":"Place a medium-sized non-stick frying pan over medium-high heat and add olive oil. Cook meatballs in batches for 10-12 minutes, or until golden and cooked through, turning occasionally."},{"content":"Transfer meatballs onto a plate lined with paper towel to drain excess oil, then serve with reserved Romesco sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Try making some Guacamole to serve with your meatballs as an alternative to the Romesco sauce (see <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em>).","The steam created by tightly wrapping the bowl with cling film will loosen the vegetable skins making them easier to peel."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 40m","10 portions"]}